quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  40,10,"Verily, those who misbelieve shall be cried out to, 'Surely, God's hatred is greater than your hatred of each other when ye were called unto the faith and misbelieved"
  40,11,"They shall say, 'Our Lord! Thou hast killed us twice, and Thou hast quickened us twice; and we do confess our sins: is there then a way for getting out"
  40,12,"That is because when God alone was proclaimed ye did disbelieve; but when partners were joined to Him ye did believe; but judgment belongs to God, the high, the great"
  40,13,"He it is who shows you His signs, and sends down to you from heaven provision; but none is mindful except him who turns repentant"
  40,14,"then call on God, being sincere in your religion to Him, averse although the misbelievers be"
  40,15,"Exalted of degrees! The Lord of the throne! He throws the spirit by His bidding upon whom He will of His servants, to give warning of the day of meeting"
  40,16,"The day when they shall be issuing forth, naught concerning them shall be hidden from God. Whose is the kingdom on that day?- God's, the one, the dominant"
  40,17,"today shall every soul be recompensed for that which it has earned. There is no wrong today; verily, God is quick at reckoning up"
  40,18,"And warn them of the day that approaches, when hearts are choking in the gullets; those who do wrong shall have no warm friend, and no intercessor who shall be obeyed"
  40,19,He knows the deceitful of eye and what men's breasts conceal
  40,20,"and God decides with truth; but those they call on beside Him do not decide at all: verily, God, He both hears and looks"